The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Friday, May 07, 2004 				 Bush apology
																								Washington, May 6 (Reuters): US President George W. Bush today told Jordans King Abdullah that he was sorry for the humiliation suffered by Iraqi prisoners and their families.																								I told him I was sorry for the humiliation suffered by Iraqi prisoners and the humiliation suffered by their families, he said. I told him I was equally sorry that people that seen those pictures didnt understand the true nature and heart of America. I assured him that Americans like me didnt appreciate what we saw. 
